# PromQL Patterns for the Monitoring Stack

## Rate and Increase

```promql
# Per-second rate over 5 minutes (most common for counters)
rate(metric_name_total[5m])

# Total increase over a time window
increase(metric_name_total[1h])
```

## Resource Usage

```promql
# CPU usage by pod in openshift-monitoring
sum by (pod) (rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total{namespace="openshift-monitoring"}[5m]))

# Memory working set by pod
sum by (pod) (container_memory_working_set_bytes{namespace="openshift-monitoring", container!=""})

# Memory as percentage of limit
container_memory_working_set_bytes{namespace="openshift-monitoring", container!=""}
  / on(pod, container) kube_pod_container_resource_limits{resource="memory", namespace="openshift-monitoring"}
```

## Availability and Health

```promql
# All targets and their up/down status
up{namespace="openshift-monitoring"}

# Scrape duration (slow scrapes may indicate issues)
scrape_duration_seconds{namespace="openshift-monitoring"}

# Targets with failed scrapes
up{namespace="openshift-monitoring"} == 0
```

## Cardinality Investigation

```promql
# Top metrics by cardinality (number of series)
topk(10, count by (__name__) ({namespace="openshift-monitoring"}))

# Series count for a specific metric
count(some_metric_name)

# Label values contributing to cardinality
count by (label_name) (some_metric_name)
```

## Alerting Pipeline

```promql
# Alerts currently firing in Prometheus
ALERTS{alertstate="firing"}

# Alert evaluation duration
prometheus_rule_group_last_duration_seconds

# Alertmanager notification failures
alertmanager_notifications_failed_total
```

## Histogram Quantiles

```promql
# p99 latency from a histogram
histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))

# p50 (median)
histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))
```

## Aggregation Patterns

```promql
# Sum across all instances, preserve job label
sum by (job) (rate(metric_total[5m]))

# Average across replicas
avg by (job) (metric_gauge)

# Max across all pods (find the worst offender)
max by (pod) (container_memory_working_set_bytes{namespace="openshift-monitoring"})
```
